-- 12-recursive-requirement-extractor.cell (R17, v0.2)
-- Takes a vague request. Extracts explicit and implicit requirements.
-- Recursively decomposes implicit requirements into sub-requirements.
-- вҠўвҲҳ loop until all requirements are concrete and testable.
--
-- Tests: вҠўвҠў spawner (recursive decomposition), вҠўвҲҳ evolution loop,
--        semantic judgment gating (depth control), oracle classification,
--        wildcard dependencies, вҠўвҲҳ-managed aspirational oracles
--
-- v0.2 changes from R16:
--   - вҠЁ? at file scope (default recovery for all cells)
--   - Wildcard deps (decomposer-*вҶ’field) now v0.2-compliant
--   - вҠўвҠў spawn-decomposers: explicit accumulate mode (v0.2 default)
--   - Oracles on extract-implicit are aspirational under вҠўвҲҳ management
--   - Guard clause on refine-vague: skips when remaining-vague is empty
--   - given? on refine-vague for graceful вҠҘ when guard skips
--   - вҠўвҲҳ parameter bindings syntax clarified per v0.2 spec
--
-- Vague request: "Build me a chat app"

вҠў request
  given text вүЎ "Build me a chat app"
  yield text

  вҠЁ text is a vague software request with unstated assumptions

вҠў extract-explicit
  given requestвҶ’text
  yield requirements[]

  вҲҙ Read В«requestвҶ’textВ» and extract every explicitly stated requirement.
    An explicit requirement is something the request directly says or
    unambiguously implies from the literal words. For "Build me a chat app":
    - "chat" = messaging between parties
    - "app" = software application
    - "build" = create from scratch (not configure existing)
    - "me" = for the requester's use/ownership

    List each as a concrete, testable statement.

  вҠЁ each requirement is directly traceable to words in the request
  вҠЁ each requirement is a testable statement (can verify pass/fail)
  вҠЁ length(requirements) вүҘ 1

вҠў extract-implicit
  given requestвҶ’text
  given extract-explicitвҶ’requirements
  yield requirements[], confidence[]

  вҲҙ Identify requirements NOT stated in В«requestвҶ’textВ» but implied by
    convention, domain knowledge, or reasonable user expectations.
    For a "chat app", implicit requirements might include:
    - User accounts (who is chatting?)
    - Message persistence (can I see old messages?)
    - Real-time delivery (do messages appear instantly?)
    - Security (are messages private?)

    For each implicit requirement, assign a confidence level:
    - certain: virtually all chat apps have this (e.g., message sending)
    - likely: most chat apps have this (e.g., read receipts)
    - possible: some chat apps have this (e.g., voice messages)

    Do NOT include requirements already in В«extract-explicitвҶ’requirementsВ».

  -- v0.2: These oracles are aspirational under вҠўвҲҳ management.
  -- They serve as feedback signals for the evolution loop, not hard gates.
  вҠЁ no requirement in implicit duplicates one in extract-explicitвҶ’requirements
  вҠЁ length(requirements) вүҘ 3
  вҠЁ each requirement has a corresponding confidence level
  вҠЁ each confidence вҲҲ {certain, likely, possible}

вҠў assess-concreteness
  given extract-explicitвҶ’requirements
  given extract-implicitвҶ’requirements
  yield concrete[], vague[], concreteness-score

  вҲҙ For each requirement from both explicit and implicit lists, judge:
    Is this requirement concrete and testable as stated?

    Concrete: "Users can send text messages up to 10,000 characters"
    Vague: "The app should be fast" (how fast? measured how?)

    Classify each as concrete or vague. Assign a concreteness score
    (0-10): ratio of concrete to total requirements.

  вҠЁ length(concrete) + length(vague) = length(extract-explicitвҶ’requirements) + length(extract-implicitвҶ’requirements)
  вҠЁ concreteness-score = 10 Г— length(concrete) / (length(concrete) + length(vague))
  вҠЁ each vague requirement explains why it's vague

вҠўвҠў spawn-decomposers
  given assess-concretenessвҶ’vague
  given В§decompose-template
  yield В§decomposer-cells[]
  until length(decomposer-cells) = length(assess-concretenessвҶ’vague)
  max 10
  -- v0.2: explicit accumulate mode (default per v0.2 spec)
  accumulate

  вҲҙ For each vague requirement in В«assess-concretenessвҶ’vagueВ», spawn
    a decomposer cell that breaks it into concrete sub-requirements.
    Each spawned cell receives the vague requirement and must produce
    testable sub-requirements that collectively satisfy the original.

  вҠЁ length(decomposer-cells) = length(assess-concretenessвҶ’vague)

вҠў decompose-template
  given requirement
  yield sub-requirements[], all-concrete

  вҲҙ The requirement В«requirementВ» is vague. Break it into specific,
    testable sub-requirements. Each sub-requirement should be concrete
    enough to verify pass/fail in a test. If a sub-requirement is still
    vague, mark all-concrete as false -- the вҠўвҲҳ loop will recurse.

    Example: "The app should be fast" вҶ’
    - "Page load time < 2 seconds on 3G connection"
    - "Message delivery latency < 500ms on broadband"
    - "Search returns results in < 1 second for up to 100k messages"

  вҠЁ each sub-requirement is more specific than the original В«requirementВ»
  вҠЁ sub-requirements collectively cover the intent of В«requirementВ»
  вҠЁ all-concrete вҲҲ {true, false}
  вҠЁ if all-concrete = true then every sub-requirement has a measurable criterion

вҠў collect-requirements
  given assess-concretenessвҶ’concrete
  given decomposer-*вҶ’sub-requirements
  given decomposer-*вҶ’all-concrete
  yield all-requirements[], remaining-vague[], completeness-score

  вҲҙ Merge the already-concrete requirements from В«assess-concretenessвҶ’concreteВ»
    with all sub-requirements from the decomposer cells.
    Check if any sub-requirements are still vague (all-concrete = false).
    Compute completeness-score:
    - 10 if all requirements are concrete
    - Lower proportional to remaining vague requirements

  вҠЁ all-requirements contains every concrete requirement and sub-requirement
  вҠЁ remaining-vague contains only requirements where all-concrete = false
  вҠЁ completeness-score = 10 if remaining-vague is empty

вҠў refine-vague
  given collect-requirementsвҶ’remaining-vague where length(remaining-vague) > 0
  given collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirements
  yield refined-requirements[]

  вҲҙ For each still-vague requirement in В«collect-requirementsвҶ’remaining-vagueВ»,
    make one more attempt to concretize it. Use the context of
    В«collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirementsВ» to inform specificity:
    if related requirements have quantitative bounds, derive bounds for
    the vague ones by analogy or convention.

  вҠЁ each refined requirement is more specific than its source in remaining-vague
  вҠЁ each refined requirement has a measurable or verifiable criterion

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(extract-implicit, requestвҶ’text, extract-explicitвҶ’requirements)
  through collect-requirements, refine-vague
  until collect-requirementsвҶ’completeness-score вүҘ 9
  max 3

  -- Each iteration: implicit requirements extracted вҶ’ concreteness assessed вҶ’
  -- vague ones decomposed by spawner вҶ’ results collected вҶ’ still-vague
  -- refined вҶ’ loop until completeness вүҘ 9 or max iterations.
  -- Recursive depth is controlled by semantic judgment in decompose-template:
  -- it marks all-concrete = false only when sub-requirements are genuinely
  -- still vague, preventing infinite recursion.
  --
  -- v0.2: extract-implicit's oracles are aspirational under вҠўвҲҳ management.
  -- The вҠўвҲҳ until condition (completeness вүҘ 9) is the actual convergence gate.

вҠў format-spec
  given collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirements
  given requestвҶ’text
  yield specification

  вҲҙ Format В«collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirementsВ» as a structured requirements
    specification document for the original request В«requestвҶ’textВ».
    Group requirements by category (functional, non-functional, security,
    UX). Number each requirement. Mark which were explicit vs implicit.

  вҠЁ specification groups requirements by category
  вҠЁ specification numbers each requirement
  вҠЁ specification marks each requirement as explicit or implicit
  вҠЁ every requirement from all-requirements appears in the specification

-- v0.2: вҠЁ? at file scope вҖ” default recovery for all cells without local вҠЁ?
вҠЁ? on failure:
  retry with В«oracle.failuresВ» appended to prompt
  max 3
вҠЁ? on exhaustion:
  partial-accept(best)
